description.narrative:
The overall goal of project is to contribute to the promotion of the mining sector for sustainable development in Burkina Faso. Specifically the project aims to:
&nbsp; -Increased voluntary investment by mining companies for the benefit of communities in the areas of basic social services (education, health).
-Promote transparency in the management of allocated resources by extractive industries.&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The problems analysis noted that Burkinabe mining sector is still booming.&nbsp; We have many operating mines under construction or constuction start. This exploitation has impact on the environment, social and economic life of the people, especially those living in areas including mining sites. Mining companies contributed to economic development of country but their contribution is below the expectations of the people. Government revised 2003 code mining to improve more contribution of companies in ongoing development process. The new code includes the creation of 03 funds as follows: a local development fund, a rehabilitation funds, securing artisanal mining sites and the fight against the use of prohibited chemicals and funding of geological and mining research funding and support for training in earth sciences. These funds will be financed by the government, mining companies and artisanal miners. But all communities who are the stakeholders don&rsquo;t know these news measures and they have a low capacity to monitor and influence their implementation. CSR has been identified as an approach to impose real development.The 2012-2015 phases helped to promote this approach with mining companies but very few still applies.Because these companies identify their contractual obligations as CSR actions. It is therefore necessary to work towards a harmonization of the concept CSR and improving knowledge of the people on this concept, for they follow, evaluate and influence the actions of CSR initiated for them.
To achieve these objectives the project actions will focus on promote CSR&nbsp;and set up community monitoring system. 
The target group is the mining companies whose actions affects environmental social and economic life of people. The project will affect the whole country but the effects of the project will be more noticeable in 04 areas where mining sites are located.&nbsp;
The main thematic focus is human right. &nbsp;
